                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Congregation Shearith Israel&#44;<lb/>
                ק״ק שארית ישראל<lb/>
                New York&#44; Nov 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5645<lb/>
                1884<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa<lb/>
                Rev &#38; Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>In behalf of the Trustees<lb/> of above Congregation&#44; I take the liberty of applying<lb/> to you for such information as you may  have&#44; or can<lb/> obtain for us&#44; regarding the character&#44; capacity &#38;c. of<lb/> the following gentlemen&#44; who have applied for the office<lb/> as set forth in Enclosed advertisement&#8212;Knowing that<lb/>you have facilities for ascertaining the necessary facts &#38;c&#44;<lb/> I feel assured that you will Excuse the trouble we<lb/> put you to&#44; in asking this favor at your hands&#8212;One of<lb/> the applicants Mr Curiel&#44; mentions your name as reference.<lb/> The persons applying are<lb/></p>
            <p>Giuseppe Curiel		Trieste<lb/>
                Marco Covcos			Livorno<lb/>
                Moise Massiah		    &#34;<lb/>
                Trever Ezechiele		Casalmonferrato<lb/></p>
            <p>Again apologising for the liberty I take&#44; and thanking you in<lb/> advance for your kindness &#38;c&#44; I remain<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Yours most Respectfully<lb/>
                Joseph Blumenthal<lb/>
                Chairman Special Committee<lb/>
                on applications for Hazan &#38;c<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Address		Room 16<lb/>
                31 Chambers St<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
